    <h3>Data Entry Speed and Efficiency Tips</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Auto-Focus on First Field:</strong> The first field is auto-focused for immediate typing without clicking.</li>
        <li><strong>Use Tab:</strong> After completing one field, press <kbd>Tab</kbd> to move to the next field quickly.</li>
        <li><strong>Use Shift + Tab:</strong> Press <kbd>Shift</kbd> + <kbd>Tab</kbd> to go back to the previous field if necessary.</li>
        <li><strong>Autocomplete:</strong> Many fields have dropdowns. Start typing, and matching options will appear for faster selection.</li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> Use the arrow keys to navigate dropdown options, and press <kbd>Tab</kbd> to select.</li>
        <li><strong>Default Values:</strong> Commonly selected fields are prefilled with default values to reduce repeated selection.</li>
        <li><strong>Save Time with Autofill:</strong> Prefilled fields or autofill features based on past data can speed up data entry.</li>
        <li><strong>Clear Form Quickly:</strong> Use <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>A</kbd> to select all text, then press <kbd>Delete</kbd> to clear. Alternatively, use the "Clear All" button to reset the form.</li>
        <li><strong>Form Validation:</strong> Look for error messages after form submission to correct missing or incorrect data.</li>
        <li><strong>Keyboard Shortcuts:</strong> Press <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>Enter</kbd> to submit the form when all required fields are filled.</li>
